# TECHNOLOGIES
## Client-side:
* NodeJS https://nodejs.org/en/download/
* MongoDB https://www.mongodb.com/download-center#atlas
* KeystoneJS http://keystonejs.com/
* SCSS http://sass-lang.com/install
* Nunjucks (for templating engine) https://mozilla.github.io/nunjucks/
* GulpJS (Not in use at the moment since KeystoneJS compiles upon runtime. It's there in case you'd like to run other * builds. Otherwise, please disregard it)

## Server-side:
* Digital Ocean
* Ubuntu 16.04 LTS
* ngix for web server and reverse proxy
* Let's Encrypt for HTTPS (autorenews. Current latest TLS 1.2 protocol)


# GETTING STARTED
Please download all client-side technologies before cloning repo. This web app follows a traditional MVC. It's a simple NodeJS app that primarily use templating engine to generate static webpages. Nunjucks is similar to Handlebars and Jade.

File structure: http://keystonejs.com/docs/getting-started/#gettingstarted-projectstructure
Our project uses .nunjucks instead of .jade. 

Login to Digital Ocean
Set up and connect via SSH
https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials/how-to-set-up-ssh-keys--2
https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials/how-to-connect-to-your-droplet-with-ssh

